00:24:18,880 --> 00:24:20,479
To discover through living together

582
00:24:20,479 --> 00:24:21,839
Rather than asking everything now

583
00:24:21,839 --> 00:24:23,199
If you just tell me who you are

584
00:24:23,199 --> 00:24:23,880
What you like

585
00:24:23,880 --> 00:24:24,439
What you dislike

586
00:24:24,439 --> 00:24:25,400
That would be boring to me

587
00:24:25,400 --> 00:24:27,880
Shouldn't we communicate clearly at the beginning

588
00:24:27,880 --> 00:24:29,439
To have a future together?

589
00:24:29,439 --> 00:24:30,680
For me personally

590
00:24:30,680 --> 00:24:32,520
When I'm into someone, I like who they are

591
00:24:32,520 --> 00:24:34,359
Whatever changes may come

592
00:24:34,359 --> 00:24:36,280
Whatever aspects I might not like later

593
00:24:36,280 --> 00:24:37,719
I'm willing to accept that consequence

594
00:24:37,719 --> 00:24:38,640
I'll make compromises

595
00:24:38,640 --> 00:24:41,000
Because when I decide, I'm committed

596
00:24:45,839 --> 00:24:47,680
I'll make nineteen, you just make one.

597
00:24:49,560 --> 00:24:51,680
I think this requires some strength.

598
00:24:51,680 --> 00:24:52,520
You focus on being beautiful.

599
00:24:52,520 --> 00:24:53,959
I'll take care of all these things.

600
00:24:56,199 --> 00:24:59,439
I think Xiao Enya is very intelligent and graceful,

601
00:24:59,439 --> 00:25:00,479
and also very, very

602
00:25:00,479 --> 00:25:01,920
a girl with a surprising contrast.

603
00:25:01,920 --> 00:25:03,640
I really, really like

604
00:25:03,640 --> 00:25:05,160
I

605
00:25:05,160 --> 00:25:07,160
like

606
00:25:07,160 --> 00:25:08,599
you.

607
00:25:16,400 --> 00:25:18,760
Do you know what I like most about you?

608
00:25:19,800 --> 00:25:21,359
I think you're a very genuine person.

609
00:25:23,040 --> 00:25:25,280
In this rather superficial society,

610
00:25:25,280 --> 00:25:27,040
many people actually put on

611
00:25:27,040 --> 00:25:31,280
this kind of external facade.

612
00:25:31,280 --> 00:25:31,800
Right.

613
00:25:31,800 --> 00:25:32,959
To be honest, truly.

614
00:25:32,959 --> 00:25:34,319
When I came to this show,

615
00:25:34,319 --> 00:25:35,800
my original intention was

616
00:25:35,800 --> 00:25:39,040
if I could find love, great,

617
00:25:39,040 --> 00:25:41,439
if not, I'd just be funny.

618
00:25:41,439 --> 00:25:42,000
So both of us

619
00:25:42,000 --> 00:25:43,560
are quite genuine people.

620
00:25:43,560 --> 00:25:45,280
Regardless of how this game

621
00:25:45,280 --> 00:25:46,959
has many setups,

622
00:25:46,959 --> 00:25:49,560
and people might have many motives,

623
00:25:49,560 --> 00:25:52,280
but we're both quite sincere.

624
00:25:52,280 --> 00:25:54,520
Even if we don't end up together, just being friends

625
00:25:54,520 --> 00:25:55,199
would make me happy.

626
00:25:55,199 --> 00:25:56,839
Even if you end up not liking me,

627
00:25:57,880 --> 00:25:58,599
that's okay.

628
00:25:58,599 --> 00:25:59,319
I won't...

629
00:25:59,319 --> 00:25:59,959
mind.

630
00:25:59,959 --> 00:26:01,719
But my point is, as long as we're happy.

631
00:26:01,719 --> 00:26:02,400
Right.

632
00:26:03,359 --> 00:26:04,680
Happy now, bro.

633
00:26:04,680 --> 00:26:05,640
Feeling blessed again, bro.

634
00:26:07,359 --> 00:26:08,319
Let me ask you one more thing.

635
00:26:08,319 --> 00:26:10,160
Are you sure you have no issues with me at all?

636
00:26:10,160 --> 00:26:12,000
Let me think harder...

637
00:26:14,719 --> 00:26:15,800
I think you liking me is enough.

638
00:26:15,800 --> 00:26:16,959
I don't think there need to be any issues.

639
00:26:16,959 --> 00:26:18,040
I just wanted to tease you.

640
00:26:18,040 --> 00:26:19,640
Didn't expect you to take it so seriously.

641
00:26:19,640 --> 00:26:20,719
Pretty funny.

642
00:26:22,079 --> 00:26:23,239
Would you go three days without washing your hair?

643
00:26:31,079 --> 00:26:32,000
It could also be five days.

644
00:26:33,040 --> 00:26:34,560
Okay, then I'll change what I said earlier.

645
00:26:34,560 --> 00:26:36,479
What's the one thing you can't stand about girls?

646
00:26:36,479 --> 00:26:38,040
Change three days to five days.

647
00:26:38,040 --> 00:26:40,000
Really, this childish emotional feeling.

648
00:26:40,000 --> 00:26:42,719
It feels like going back to puppy love in adolescence.

649
00:26:42,719 --> 00:26:45,319
I think there's actually an opportunity now.

650
00:26:45,319 --> 00:26:46,560
For me to find love.

651
00:26:46,560 --> 00:26:47,920
But it's not love yet.

652
00:26:47,920 --> 00:26:50,040
It's just affection and liking.

653
00:26:50,040 --> 00:26:52,040
In just ten short days.

654
00:26:52,040 --> 00:26:53,479
You're asking me to say "I love you."

655
00:26:53,479 --> 00:26:54,800
"I love you so much."

656
00:26:54,800 --> 00:26:56,359
That would be irresponsible to others.

657
00:26:56,359 --> 00:26:57,359
But getting this chance.

658
00:26:57,359 --> 00:26:58,280
Has already been hard enough to come by.

659
00:26:58,280 --> 00:26:59,359
So I'll cherish it properly.

660
00:26:59,359 --> 00:27:01,280
Super happy, super joyful.

661
00:27:01,280 --> 00:27:03,800
I'll keep striving for love.

662
00:27:03,800 --> 00:27:05,199
Let's toast and wrap it up.

663
00:27:05,199 --> 00:27:07,119
Did you enjoy today's date?

664
00:27:07,119 --> 00:27:08,040
The food was okay.

665
00:27:08,040 --> 00:27:11,359
But the person... I might need to think about it more.

666
00:27:11,359 --> 00:27:12,760
Then you'd better hurry up.

667
00:27:26,359 --> 00:27:27,560
What do you usually like to do?

668
00:27:28,959 --> 00:27:29,800
What do I like to do?

669
00:27:31,319 --> 00:27:32,959
I seem to have quite a few things I enjoy doing.

670
00:27:32,959 --> 00:27:34,599
I can't stay idle.

671
00:27:34,599 --> 00:27:35,439
That's good.

672
00:27:36,839 --> 00:27:39,239
Actually, last night I really felt vulnerable.

673
00:27:39,239 --> 00:27:40,719
I was really lying in bed thinking...

674
00:27:40,719 --> 00:27:41,959
Why did I come back?

675
00:27:41,959 --> 00:27:43,319
I was genuinely thinking about this.

676
00:27:43,319 --> 00:27:44,079
Last night...

677
00:27:45,239 --> 00:27:47,959
Yesterday I noticed you kept sighing.

678
00:27:47,959 --> 00:27:49,239
Yes, actually at yesterday's gathering...

679
00:27:49,239 --> 00:27:50,359
Everyone was so happy.

680
00:27:50,359 --> 00:27:52,800
I was only happy for a few moments.

681
00:27:52,800 --> 00:27:53,839
The rest of the time I felt detached.

682
00:27:53,839 --> 00:27:54,680
You know what?

683
00:27:54,680 --> 00:27:56,040
I think... what should I do?

684
00:27:56,040 --> 00:27:57,880
How do I fit in? How should I blend with everyone?

685
00:28:00,239 --> 00:28:02,400
That's why I feel coming here might not work.

686
00:28:02,400 --> 00:28:03,880
Because my friends around me...

687
00:28:03,880 --> 00:28:05,599
You can do it. You've got this.

688
00:28:05,599 --> 00:28:07,719
You can do it. You've got this.

689
00:28:07,719 --> 00:28:09,239
Can I really?

690
00:28:09,239 --> 00:28:09,839
Thank you.

691
00:28:09,839 --> 00:28:10,839
You can do it.

692
00:28:10,839 --> 00:28:13,800
I really rely on your encouragement.

693
00:28:15,760 --> 00:28:18,079
So, would you think for example...

694
00:28:18,079 --> 00:28:19,560
If I asked you to team up,

695
00:28:19,560 --> 00:28:21,280
Or showed you preferential treatment...

696
00:28:21,280 --> 00:28:22,719
Would you think that's okay?

697
00:28:22,719 --> 00:28:23,439
Yes.

698
00:28:23,439 --> 00:28:24,079
Okay.

699
00:28:24,079 --> 00:28:25,359
I'm very happy today.

700
00:28:25,359 --> 00:28:26,439
Thank you.

701
00:28:26,439 --> 00:28:27,800
I feel so relieved.

702
00:28:27,800 --> 00:28:29,680
This is how I feel now.

703
00:28:29,680 --> 00:28:31,280
Today I feel like a weight has been lifted.

704
00:28:36,160 --> 00:28:38,280
The little pig I raised as a child could swim.

705
00:28:39,400 --> 00:28:40,199
Every day,

706
00:28:40,199 --> 00:28:41,119
it would swim.

707
00:28:41,119 --> 00:28:42,359
I would take it for walks.

708
00:28:42,359 --> 00:28:44,079
While others walked their dogs, we walked our pig.

709
00:28:44,079 --> 00:28:45,839
We strolled with our pig.

710
00:28:45,839 --> 00:28:47,599
Then we’d go to the seaside,

711
00:28:47,599 --> 00:28:49,880
toss it into the water and let it swim back up.

712
00:28:49,880 --> 00:28:50,920
It would get so annoyed,

713
00:28:50,920 --> 00:28:52,119
like this—

714
00:28:52,119 --> 00:28:53,520
shaking its tail as it climbed out.

715
00:28:54,599 --> 00:28:56,520
As soon as it caught its breath, I’d throw it back in.

716
00:28:57,520 --> 00:28:58,640
Three or four times a day.

717
00:28:58,640 --> 00:28:59,520
So mean.

718
00:28:59,520 --> 00:29:00,560
Its squeals were adorable—

719
00:29:02,319 --> 00:29:03,800
it sounded like this:

720
00:29:03,800 --> 00:29:04,880
"I am a pig!"

721
00:29:07,119 --> 00:29:08,800
It only made that noise when eating.

722
00:29:08,800 --> 00:29:09,280
Normally, it was...

723
00:29:10,560 --> 00:29:12,119
Every bite makes a sound when eating.

724
00:29:12,119 --> 00:29:13,079
It goes like this.

725
00:29:13,079 --> 00:29:14,760
When it eats, it really does this.

726
00:29:21,000 --> 00:29:22,800
I've had moments in relationships

727
00:29:22,800 --> 00:29:24,800
where I struggled deeply

728
00:29:24,800 --> 00:29:25,760
For instance,

729
00:29:25,760 --> 00:29:29,119
when torn between new beginnings and past attachments,

730
00:29:32,000 --> 00:29:33,959
I went nearly six years without

731
00:29:33,959 --> 00:29:36,359
a steady romantic relationship.

732
00:29:36,359 --> 00:29:39,439
There were only casual acquaintances,

733
00:29:39,439 --> 00:29:41,239
kept in sporadic contact,

734
00:29:41,239 --> 00:29:43,319
until they eventually married others.

735
00:29:48,560 --> 00:29:49,599
Not dating for six years

736
00:29:49,599 --> 00:29:51,280
Don't you feel lonely?

737
00:29:51,280 --> 00:29:51,959
No.

738
00:29:51,959 --> 00:29:53,560
Actually, most of the time,

739
00:29:53,560 --> 00:29:56,239
I don’t think much about relationships.

740
00:29:56,239 --> 00:29:58,319
I have family and friends

741
00:29:58,319 --> 00:30:00,199
filling my time.

742
00:30:00,199 --> 00:30:00,920
That’s why

743
00:30:00,920 --> 00:30:03,000
you wanted to join this show?

744
00:30:03,000 --> 00:30:04,479
That’s one reason.

745
00:30:04,479 --> 00:30:07,800
I feel I need new social connections.

746
00:30:09,239 --> 00:30:10,479
I want to make some changes.

747
00:30:11,920 --> 00:30:12,719
Even if coming here

748
00:30:12,719 --> 00:30:14,719
just means meeting new people.

749
00:30:27,599 --> 00:30:28,920
Read after me

750
00:30:39,239 --> 00:30:39,760
Too long

751
00:30:42,319 --> 00:30:43,640
Our meeting is also fate

752
00:30:43,640 --> 00:30:45,239
Go back and send me your address.

753
00:30:45,239 --> 00:30:46,880
I'll give you a wooden guitar from my home.

754
00:30:46,880 --> 00:30:47,920
Really.

755
00:30:47,920 --> 00:30:49,280
Because I want you to keep going.

756
00:30:49,280 --> 00:30:50,479
I think you have talent

757
00:30:50,479 --> 00:30:51,239
Really?

758
00:30:57,599 --> 00:30:59,400
We make such an amazing pair of friends.

759
00:31:00,800 --> 00:31:02,160
I feel like coming to this show was totally worth it.

760
00:31:02,160 --> 00:31:02,520
Really.

761
00:31:02,520 --> 00:31:03,760
Yeah, okay.

762
00:31:05,599 --> 00:31:07,400
Because I have no expectations for love anymore.

763
00:31:07,400 --> 00:31:09,000
But I think...

764
00:31:09,000 --> 00:31:10,839
Okay, I get it. No need to say more. Let's practice.

765
00:31:10,839 --> 00:31:12,160
Why do I suddenly feel a bit moved?

766
00:31:13,479 --> 00:31:14,160
You go ahead and practice.

767
00:31:16,119 --> 00:31:17,319
Actually, I'm really...

768
00:31:17,319 --> 00:31:19,439
sometimes a very emotionally sensitive person.

769
00:31:19,439 --> 00:31:20,160
I know.

770
00:31:20,160 --> 00:31:20,680
You understand, right?

771
00:31:20,680 --> 00:31:21,280
I know.

772
00:31:21,280 --> 00:31:22,239
You probably understand me quite well.

773
00:31:22,239 --> 00:31:22,800
I know.

774
00:31:25,439 --> 00:31:26,640
She can play the guitar.

775
00:31:26,640 --> 00:31:27,959
She even taught me how to play.

776
00:31:27,959 --> 00:31:30,640
I know this island's main theme is romance,

777
00:31:30,640 --> 00:31:33,479
but I feel like I've gained a lot of friendship here.

778
00:31:33,479 --> 00:31:34,680
It's not just about romance.

779
00:31:58,800 --> 00:31:59,160
Let's hold hands

780
00:32:00,520 --> 00:32:00,959
Three

781
00:32:00,959 --> 00:32:02,000
Let's hold hands after we get over there

782
00:32:02,000 --> 00:32:02,719
Two

783
00:32:02,719 --> 00:32:03,520
Let's hold hands right here

784
00:32:03,520 --> 00:32:04,280
Why?

785
00:32:04,280 --> 00:32:05,119
Hold hands there

786
00:32:05,119 --> 00:32:05,560
It's the same

787
00:32:07,239 --> 00:32:07,680
I don't want to

788
00:32:07,680 --> 00:32:09,640
I feel like my soul has been drained

789
00:32:15,719 --> 00:32:17,640
If you keep resisting, I'll "call the police"

790
00:32:17,640 --> 00:32:18,359
Go ahead and "call the police"

791
00:32:18,359 --> 00:32:18,959
I'll do it right now

792
00:32:23,000 --> 00:32:24,880
You're really "going crazy"

793
00:32:24,880 --> 00:32:25,880
I'm jealous

794
00:32:25,880 --> 00:32:26,400
Let me tell you

795
00:32:26,400 --> 00:32:26,959
Someone like me

796
00:32:28,319 --> 00:32:28,719
That's just how it is

797
00:32:29,839 --> 00:32:31,400
What do you have to be jealous about?

798
00:32:31,400 --> 00:32:32,280
I feel

799
00:32:32,280 --> 00:32:34,719
It feels like you don't value this ring

800
00:32:34,719 --> 00:32:35,439
You're not single

801
00:32:38,040 --> 00:32:38,680
Change the ring

802
00:32:42,520 --> 00:32:43,800
This one doesn't look good

803
00:32:43,800 --> 00:32:44,479
It looks fine

804
00:32:44,479 --> 00:32:45,719
This is superstition

805
00:32:56,000 --> 00:32:57,160
What happened to us this morning

806
00:32:57,160 --> 00:32:58,079
The rings we wore yesterday

807
00:32:58,079 --> 00:32:59,439
I told her very clearly yesterday

808
00:32:59,439 --> 00:33:00,359
that we'd wear rings today

809
00:33:00,359 --> 00:33:01,239
and go back together

810
00:33:01,239 --> 00:33:03,000
to show off to everyone

811
00:33:03,000 --> 00:33:03,680
And then?

812
00:33:03,680 --> 00:33:05,040
Then she didn't wear it

813
00:33:05,040 --> 00:33:06,560
Actually, I want to explain to everyone

814
00:33:06,560 --> 00:33:07,959
why the ring wasn't worn

815
00:33:07,959 --> 00:33:11,160
It's because my other jewelry didn't match well

816
00:33:11,160 --> 00:33:11,880
so I left it there

817
00:33:11,880 --> 00:33:13,520
So I casually said

818
00:33:13,520 --> 00:33:15,040
I was afraid of losing it

819
00:33:15,040 --> 00:33:17,040
Then he misunderstood me

820
00:33:17,040 --> 00:33:18,239
How could I possibly lose

821
00:33:18,239 --> 00:33:20,119
the rings we made for each other?

822
00:33:20,119 --> 00:33:20,560
If it got lost

823
00:33:20,560 --> 00:33:25,160
wouldn't that mean I didn't value it enough?

824
00:33:25,160 --> 00:33:26,000
Right?

825
00:33:26,000 --> 00:33:28,119
You all know I'm very forgetful

826
00:33:28,119 --> 00:33:29,359
Look, things on my hands

827
00:33:29,359 --> 00:33:30,400
sometimes just get lost easily

828
00:33:30,400 --> 00:33:31,760
It's really normal

829
00:33:31,760 --> 00:33:33,079
But later

830
00:33:33,079 --> 00:33:33,959
Anyway, it doesn't matter

831
00:33:33,959 --> 00:33:35,880
I ended up wearing it later

832
00:33:35,880 --> 00:33:36,160
Right

833
00:33:36,160 --> 00:33:37,160
Then why get angry?

834
00:33:38,520 --> 00:33:40,040
Do you think I should be angry?

835
00:33:40,040 --> 00:33:40,400
Right

836
00:33:40,400 --> 00:33:41,839
Camera, don't you think I should be angry?

837
00:33:41,839 --> 00:33:43,119
Okay, then I won't be angry

838
00:33:47,400 --> 00:33:49,040
"Help"

839
00:33:49,040 --> 00:33:49,560
So friends

840
00:33:49,560 --> 00:33:50,760
don't you also think

841
00:33:51,959 --> 00:33:52,839
this is hard to judge

842
00:34:03,839 --> 00:34:04,959
Let me tell you

843
00:34:04,959 --> 00:34:08,560
I actually value the courting process quite a bit

844
00:34:08,560 --> 00:34:10,560
I didn't really believe in it before

845
00:34:10,560 --> 00:34:13,280
Because I thought love at first sight

846
00:34:13,280 --> 00:34:15,199
would mean staying together forever

847
00:34:15,199 --> 00:34:16,919
But getting together quickly through love at first sight

848
00:34:16,919 --> 00:34:18,600
feels just like a flash marriage

849
00:34:18,600 --> 00:34:20,520
If the flash marriage is right, it might last a lifetime

850
00:34:20,520 --> 00:34:22,159
But if it's wrong, then it's just...

851
00:34:23,840 --> 00:34:24,639
The same goes for relationships

852
00:34:24,639 --> 00:34:26,639
If you don't like fast-food style relationships

853
00:34:26,639 --> 00:34:28,520
This is something you need to consider, right?

854
00:34:30,040 --> 00:34:30,840
That's true

855
00:34:30,840 --> 00:34:31,280
Right

856
00:34:31,280 --> 00:34:31,879
So

857
00:34:31,879 --> 00:34:32,239
Yes

858
00:34:32,239 --> 00:34:34,000
I hope we can

859
00:34:34,000 --> 00:34:35,280
control the pace

860
00:34:35,280 --> 00:34:37,560
This is also a reason

861
00:34:37,560 --> 00:34:39,080
I didn't know before

862
00:34:39,080 --> 00:34:40,639
how to express this

863
00:34:40,639 --> 00:34:42,520
But it's not rejection

864
00:34:42,520 --> 00:34:44,399
I just think this is a

865
